    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then boil a full kettle</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>chicken </strong>and<strong> ground cumin </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken </strong>and cook for 3 min on each side or until lightly browned</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve<strong> </strong>your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 75m<span class=\"text-purple\">l [100ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [130ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and cook, covered, for a further 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter!), then chop the <strong>zested lime[s] </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> with a little drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> lime zest </strong>and the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lime[s] </strong>in a large bowl</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coriander dressing</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomato</strong> in the bowl with the dressing and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> zingy corn salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, add the juice of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime </strong>and cook for 1 min</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and shred the chicken apart, using two forks \u2013 this is your <strong>Peruvian-style chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/peruvian-style-chicken-rice-bowl-with-zingy-corn-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Peruvian-style chicken</strong> with the <strong>brown rice </strong>and <strong>zingy corn salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Top with your <strong>pine kernel and seed mix</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
